Search in command line (post login to server via terminal) 
yum search php71-mbstring
php71-mbstring.x86_64

php-mysqlnd.x86_64
php71-pdo.x86_64

yum install all the above.

#to view errors-- Needs to be in directory cd /var/log/httpd/
tail -f error_log 
vim error_log to change 

use whereis to find things within terminal for php

eg whereis php.ini
then go to cd /etc
vim php.ini
find keyword error, type n for next search, x for delete a word. 
Edit log_errors = Off to log_errors = On
key in “:” then qa to save and quit